# Repo overview

Personal **NeetCode / LeetCode-style** solutions by `@iamadityasharma92`.

## Layout

- Workspace root: `GIT-DSA/` (Cursor workspace; not a git root).
- Git repo: `DSA/` → `https://github.com/iamadityasharma92/DSA.git`
- Solutions live only under:

```
DSA/Data Structures & Algorithms/<problem-slug>/submission-N.java
```

- ~90+ problem folders; language is **Java only**.
- Problem slugs are NeetCode kebab-case (e.g. `two-integer-sum`, `permutation-string`).
- Multiple `submission-N.java` files = iterative attempts (higher N is usually later/better).

## Agent defaults

- Help with understanding, debugging, optimizing, or writing the next submission.
- Prefer adding `submission-(max+1).java` over overwriting older attempts unless asked.
- Match existing compact style; do not add packages, build systems, or project scaffolding.
- Explain time/space complexity when proposing a solution.
- Git root for commits is `DSA/`, not the workspace root. Only commit when explicitly asked.
- Commit message style: `Add: <problem-slug> - submission-N` or `Update: <problem-slug> - submission-N`.
